==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underfong
<hw>Un`der*fong"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>underfongen</ets>, p. p. of <ets>underf⟦omac⟧n</ets> to undertake;
<ets>under</ets> under + <ets>f⟦omac⟧n</ets> to take. See <er>Fang</er>
to seize.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To undertake; to take in hand; to
receive.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au> <au>Rom.
of R.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To insnare; to circumvent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To sustain; to support; to guard.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Nash.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underfoot</ent>⟦br⟧
